                    "view": "user_course_progress",
                    "schema": "public",
                    "definition": " SELECT c.id,\n    c.title,\n    c.description,\n    c.slug,\n    c.cover_image_url,\n    c.thumbnail_url,\n    c.category,\n    c.difficulty,\n    c.is_published,\n    c.created_at,\n    c.updated_at,\n    COALESCE(progress_data.user_id, auth.uid()) AS user_id,\n    COALESCE(progress_data.total_lessons, 0::bigint) AS total_lessons,\n    COALESCE(progress_data.completed_lessons, 0::bigint) AS completed_lessons,\n    COALESCE(progress_data.completion_percentage, 0::double precision) AS completion_percentage,\n    progress_data.last_activity_at,\n    jsonb_build_object('completed', COALESCE(progress_data.completed_lessons, 0::bigint), 'total', COALESCE(progress_data.total_lessons, 0::bigint), 'percentage', COALESCE(progress_data.completion_percentage, 0::double precision), 'lastActivityAt', progress_data.last_activity_at, 'status', COALESCE(progress_data.status, 'not_started'::text)) AS progress\n   FROM courses c\n     LEFT JOIN ( SELECT m.course_id,\n            count(l.id) AS total_lessons,\n            count(\n                CASE\n                    WHEN up.status = 'completed'::text THEN 1\n                    ELSE NULL::integer\n                END) AS completed_lessons,\n            round(\n                CASE\n                    WHEN count(l.id) > 0 THEN count(\n                    CASE\n                        WHEN up.status = 'completed'::text THEN 1\n                        ELSE NULL::integer\n                    END)::double precision / count(l.id)::double precision * 100::double precision\n                    ELSE 0::double precision\n                END) AS completion_percentage,\n            max(up.updated_at) AS last_activity_at,\n            up.user_id,\n                CASE\n                    WHEN count(\n                    CASE\n                        WHEN up.status = 'completed'::text THEN 1\n                        ELSE NULL::integer\n                    END) = 0 THEN 'not_started'::text\n                    WHEN count(\n                    CASE\n                        WHEN up.status = 'completed'::text THEN 1\n                        ELSE NULL::integer\n                    END) = count(l.id) THEN 'completed'::text\n                    ELSE 'in_progress'::text\n                END AS status\n           FROM modules m\n             JOIN lessons l ON l.module_id = m.id\n             LEFT JOIN user_progress up ON up.lesson_id = l.id AND up.user_id = auth.uid()\n          WHERE m.is_published = true AND l.is_published = true\n          GROUP BY m.course_id, up.user_id) progress_data ON progress_data.course_id = c.id\n  WHERE c.is_published = true;"
                },

            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION extensions.grant_pg_cron_access()\n RETURNS event_trigger\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nBEGIN\n  IF EXISTS (\n    SELECT\n    FROM pg_event_trigger_ddl_commands() AS ev\n    JOIN pg_extension AS ext\n    ON ev.objid = ext.oid\n    WHERE ext.extname = 'pg_cron'\n  )\n  THEN\n    grant usage on schema cron to postgres with grant option;\n\n    alter default privileges in schema cron grant all on tables to postgres with grant option;\n    alter default privileges in schema cron grant all on functions to postgres with grant option;\n    alter default privileges in schema cron grant all on sequences to postgres with grant option;\n\n    alter default privileges for user supabase_admin in schema cron grant all\n        on sequences to postgres with grant option;\n    alter default privileges for user supabase_admin in schema cron grant all\n        on tables to postgres with grant option;\n    alter default privileges for user supabase_admin in schema cron grant all\n        on functions to postgres with grant option;\n\n    grant all privileges on all tables in schema cron to postgres with grant option;\n    revoke all on table cron.job from postgres;\n    grant select on table cron.job to postgres with grant option;\n  END IF;\nEND;\n$function$\n"

            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION extensions.grant_pg_graphql_access()\n RETURNS event_trigger\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n    func_is_graphql_resolve bool;\nBEGIN\n    func_is_graphql_resolve = (\n        SELECT n.proname = 'resolve'\n        FROM pg_event_trigger_ddl_commands() AS ev\n        LEFT JOIN pg_catalog.pg_proc AS n\n        ON ev.objid = n.oid\n    );\n\n    IF func_is_graphql_resolve\n    THEN\n        -- Update public wrapper to pass all arguments through to the pg_graphql resolve func\n        DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS graphql_public.graphql;\n        create or replace function graphql_public.graphql(\n            \"operationName\" text default null,\n            query text default null,\n            variables jsonb default null,\n            extensions jsonb default null\n        )\n            returns jsonb\n            language sql\n        as $$\n            select graphql.resolve(\n                query := query,\n                variables := coalesce(variables, '{}'),\n                \"operationName\" := \"operationName\",\n                extensions := extensions\n            );\n        $$;\n\n        -- This hook executes when `graphql.resolve` is created. That is not necessarily the last\n        -- function in the extension so we need to grant permissions on existing entities AND\n        -- update default permissions to any others that are created after `graphql.resolve`\n        grant usage on schema graphql to postgres, anon, authenticated, service_role;\n        grant select on all tables in schema graphql to postgres, anon, authenticated, service_role;\n        grant execute on all functions in schema graphql to postgres, anon, authenticated, service_role;\n        grant all on all sequences in schema graphql to postgres, anon, authenticated, service_role;\n        alter default privileges in schema graphql grant all on tables to postgres, anon, authenticated, service_role;\n        alter default privileges in schema graphql grant all on functions to postgres, anon, authenticated, service_role;\n        alter default privileges in schema graphql grant all on sequences to postgres, anon, authenticated, service_role;\n\n        -- Allow postgres role to allow granting usage on graphql and graphql_public schemas to custom roles\n        grant usage on schema graphql_public to postgres with grant option;\n        grant usage on schema graphql to postgres with grant option;\n    END IF;\n\nEND;\n$function$\n"

pg_event_trigger_ddl_commands() AS ev\n      JOIN pg_extension AS ext\n      ON ev.objid = ext.oid\n      WHERE ext.extname = 'pg_net'\n    )\n    THEN\n      GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA net TO supabase_functions_admin, postgres, anon, authenticated, service_role;\n\n      IF EXISTS (\n        SELECT FROM pg_extension\n        WHERE extname = 'pg_net'\n        -- all versions in use on existing projects as of 2025-02-20\n        -- version 0.12.0 onwards don't need these applied\n        AND extversion IN ('0.2', '0.6', '0.7', '0.7.1', '0.8', '0.10.0', '0.11.0')\n      ) THEN\n        ALTER function net.http_get(url text, params jsonb, headers jsonb, timeout_milliseconds integer) SECURITY DEFINER;\n        ALTER function net.http_post(url text, body jsonb, params jsonb, headers jsonb, timeout_milliseconds integer) SECURITY DEFINER;\n\n        ALTER function net.http_get(url text, params jsonb, headers jsonb, timeout_milliseconds integer) SET search_path = net;\n        ALTER function net.http_post(url text, body jsonb, params jsonb, headers jsonb, timeout_milliseconds integer) SET search_path = net;\n\n        REVOKE ALL ON FUNCTION net.http_get(url text, params jsonb, headers jsonb, timeout_milliseconds integer) FROM PUBLIC;\n        REVOKE ALL ON FUNCTION net.http_post(url text, body jsonb, params jsonb, headers jsonb, timeout_milliseconds integer) FROM PUBLIC;\n\n        GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION net.http_get(url text, params jsonb, headers jsonb, timeout_milliseconds integer) TO supabase_functions_admin, postgres, anon, authenticated, service_role;\n        GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION net.http_post(url text, body jsonb, params jsonb, headers jsonb, timeout_milliseconds integer) TO supabase_functions_admin, postgres, anon, authenticated, service_role;\n      END IF;\n    END IF;\n  END;\n  $function$\n"

            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION extensions.pgrst_ddl_watch()\n RETURNS event_trigger\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  cmd record;\nBEGIN\n  FOR cmd IN SELECT * FROM pg_event_trigger_ddl_commands()\n  LOOP\n    IF cmd.command_tag IN (\n      'CREATE SCHEMA', 'ALTER SCHEMA'\n    , 'CREATE TABLE', 'CREATE TABLE AS', 'SELECT INTO', 'ALTER TABLE'\n    , 'CREATE FOREIGN TABLE', 'ALTER FOREIGN TABLE'\n    , 'CREATE VIEW', 'ALTER VIEW'\n    , 'CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW', 'ALTER MATERIALIZED VIEW'\n    , 'CREATE FUNCTION', 'ALTER FUNCTION'\n    , 'CREATE TRIGGER'\n    , 'CREATE TYPE', 'ALTER TYPE'\n    , 'CREATE RULE'\n    , 'COMMENT'\n    )\n    -- don't notify in case of CREATE TEMP table or other objects created on pg_temp\n    AND cmd.schema_name is distinct from 'pg_temp'\n    THEN\n      NOTIFY pgrst, 'reload schema';\n    END IF;\n  END LOOP;\nEND; $function$\n"

            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION net.http_delete(url text, params jsonb DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb, headers jsonb DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb, timeout_milliseconds integer DEFAULT 5000)\n RETURNS bigint\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n PARALLEL SAFE STRICT\nAS $function$\ndeclare\n    request_id bigint;\n    params_array text[];\nbegin\n    select coalesce(array_agg(net._urlencode_string(key) || '=' || net._urlencode_string(value)), '{}')\n    into params_array\n    from jsonb_each_text(params);\n\n    -- Add to the request queue\n    insert into net.http_request_queue(method, url, headers, timeout_milliseconds)\n    values (\n        'DELETE',\n        net._encode_url_with_params_array(url, params_array),\n        headers,\n        timeout_milliseconds\n    )\n    returning id\n    into request_id;\n\n    return request_id;\nend\n$function$\n"

            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION net.http_post(url text, body jsonb DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb, params jsonb DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb, headers jsonb DEFAULT '{\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}'::jsonb, timeout_milliseconds integer DEFAULT 5000)\n RETURNS bigint\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n PARALLEL SAFE\nAS $function$\ndeclare\n    request_id bigint;\n    params_array text[];\n    content_type text;\nbegin\n\n    -- Exctract the content_type from headers\n    select\n        header_value into content_type\n    from\n        jsonb_each_text(coalesce(headers, '{}'::jsonb)) r(header_name, header_value)\n    where\n        lower(header_name) = 'content-type'\n    limit\n        1;\n\n    -- If the user provided new headers and omitted the content type\n    -- add it back in automatically\n    if content_type is null then\n        select headers || '{\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}'::jsonb into headers;\n    end if;\n\n    -- Confirm that the content-type is set as \"application/json\"\n    if content_type <> 'application/json' then\n        raise exception 'Content-Type header must be \"application/json\"';\n    end if;\n\n    select\n        coalesce(array_agg(net._urlencode_string(key) || '=' || net._urlencode_string(value)), '{}')\n    into\n        params_array\n    from\n        jsonb_each_text(params);\n\n    -- Add to the request queue\n    insert into net.http_request_queue(method, url, headers, body, timeout_milliseconds)\n    values (\n        'POST',\n        net._encode_url_with_params_array(url, params_array),\n        headers,\n        convert_to(body::text, 'UTF8'),\n        timeout_milliseconds\n    )\n    returning id\n    into request_id;\n\n    return request_id;\nend\n$function$\n"

            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.ach_defs_sync_validity()\n RETURNS trigger\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nBEGIN\n  -- Si effective_from et effective_to sont fournis, synchroniser validity\n  IF NEW.effective_from IS NOT NULL AND NEW.effective_to IS NOT NULL THEN\n    IF NEW.effective_to <= NEW.effective_from THEN\n      RAISE EXCEPTION 'effective_to must be > effective_from';\n    END IF;\n    NEW.validity := tstzrange(NEW.effective_from, NEW.effective_to, '[)');\n  -- Si validity est fourni, extraire effective_from/to\n  ELSIF NEW.validity IS NOT NULL THEN\n    NEW.effective_from := lower(NEW.validity);\n    NEW.effective_to   := upper(NEW.validity);\n  END IF;\n  RETURN NEW;\nEND $function$\n"

            "function": "admin_compensate_achievement",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.admin_compensate_achievement(p_code text, p_version integer, p_reason text, p_idempotency_key text)\n RETURNS TABLE(affected_users integer, total_events integer, total_xp_reverted integer)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SECURITY DEFINER\n SET search_path TO 'pg_catalog', 'public'\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  v_achievement_def RECORD;\n  v_user_record RECORD;\n  v_affected_count int := 0;\n  v_event_count int := 0;\n  v_total_xp_delta int := 0;\n  v_new_xp int;\n  v_new_level int;\nBEGIN\n  -- 1. Validation paramtres\n  IF p_code IS NULL OR p_version IS NULL OR p_reason IS NULL OR p_idempotency_key IS NULL THEN\n    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Tous les paramtres sont obligatoires';\n  END IF;\n\n  -- 2. Vrifier achievement_definition existe\n  SELECT * INTO v_achievement_def \n  FROM public.achievement_definitions \n  WHERE code = p_code AND version = p_version;\n  \n  IF NOT FOUND THEN\n    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Achievement non trouv: % v%', p_code, p_version;\n  END IF;\n\n  -- 3. Vrifier qu'il y a des user_achievements  compenser\n  IF NOT EXISTS(\n    SELECT 1 FROM public.user_achievements \n    WHERE achievement_code = p_code AND achievement_version = p_version\n  ) THEN\n    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Aucun utilisateur n''a unlocked cet achievement: % v%', p_code, p_version;\n  END IF;\n\n  -- 4. Pour chaque utilisateur ayant unlocked cet achievement\n  FOR v_user_record IN \n    SELECT ua.user_id, ua.id as ua_id, p.xp as current_xp, p.level as current_level\n    FROM public.user_achievements ua\n    JOIN public.profiles p ON p.id = ua.user_id\n    WHERE ua.achievement_code = p_code AND ua.achievement_version = p_version\n  LOOP\n    v_affected_count := v_affected_count + 1;\n    \n    -- 5. Calculer nouveau XP (retirer le reward)\n    IF v_achievement_def.xp_reward > 0 THEN\n      v_new_xp := GREATEST(0, v_user_record.current_xp - v_achievement_def.xp_reward);\n      v_total_xp_delta := v_total_xp_delta + v_achievement_def.xp_reward;\n      \n      -- Recalculer niveau bas sur nouveau XP\n      SELECT level INTO v_new_level\n      FROM public.level_definitions\n      WHERE xp_required <= v_new_xp\n      ORDER BY xp_required DESC\n      LIMIT 1;\n      \n      IF v_new_level IS NULL THEN\n        v_new_level := 1;\n      END IF;\n\n      -- Mettre  jour profiles\n      UPDATE public.profiles \n      SET \n        xp = v_new_xp,\n        level = v_new_level,\n        last_xp_event_at = NOW()\n      WHERE id = v_user_record.user_id;\n\n      -- Crer xp_event de compensation (delta ngatif)\n      INSERT INTO public.xp_events (\n        user_id, source_type, action_type, \n        xp_delta, xp_before, xp_after,\n        level_before, level_after,\n        metadata\n      ) VALUES (\n        v_user_record.user_id, 'achievement', 'admin_compensate',\n        -v_achievement_def.xp_reward, v_user_record.current_xp, v_new_xp,\n        v_user_record.current_level, v_new_level,\n        jsonb_build_object(\n          'achievement_code', p_code,\n          'achievement_version', p_version,\n          'compensation_reason', p_reason,\n          'idempotency_key', p_idempotency_key,\n          'admin_action', true\n        )\n      );\n      \n      v_event_count := v_event_count + 1;\n    END IF;\n  END LOOP;\n\n  -- 6. Supprimer tous les user_achievements pour cet achievement\n  DELETE FROM public.user_achievements \n  WHERE achievement_code = p_code AND achievement_version = p_version;\n\n  -- 7. Optionnel: dsactiver l'achievement_definition\n  UPDATE public.achievement_definitions \n  SET \n    is_active = false,\n    updated_at = NOW()\n  WHERE code = p_code AND version = p_version;\n\n  -- 8. Log admin action\n  INSERT INTO public.admin_action_log (\n    action_type, target_type, target_id,\n    details, performed_at\n  ) VALUES (\n    'compensate_achievement', 'achievement_definition', v_achievement_def.id::text,\n    jsonb_build_object(\n      'code', p_code,\n      'version', p_version,\n      'reason', p_reason,\n      'affected_users', v_affected_count,\n      'total_xp_reverted', v_total_xp_delta,\n      'idempotency_key', p_idempotency_key\n    ),\n    NOW()\n  );\n\n  -- 9. Retourner rsultats\n  affected_users := v_affected_count;\n  total_events := v_event_count;\n  total_xp_reverted := v_total_xp_delta;\n  \n  RETURN NEXT;\nEND;\n$function$\n"

            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.compute_level(xp_total integer)\n RETURNS integer\n LANGUAGE sql\n STABLE\nAS $function$\n    SELECT COALESCE(\n        (SELECT level FROM level_definitions \n         WHERE xp_required <= xp_total \n         ORDER BY level DESC \n         LIMIT 1), \n        1\n    );\n$function$\n"

            "args": "p_xp_total integer",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "TABLE(level integer, xp_threshold integer, xp_to_next integer)",
            "function": "compute_level_info",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.compute_level_info(p_xp_total integer)\n RETURNS TABLE(level integer, xp_threshold integer, xp_to_next integer)\n LANGUAGE sql\n STABLE\nAS $function$\n  WITH defs AS (\n    SELECT \n      level, \n      xp_required,\n      LEAD(xp_required) OVER (ORDER BY level) AS next_required\n    FROM level_definitions\n    ORDER BY level\n  ),\n  pick AS (\n    SELECT *\n    FROM defs\n    WHERE xp_required <= p_xp_total\n    ORDER BY level DESC\n    LIMIT 1\n  )\n  SELECT\n    COALESCE(pick.level, 1) AS level,\n    COALESCE(pick.xp_required, 0) AS xp_threshold,\n    CASE\n      WHEN pick.next_required IS NULL THEN NULL -- niveau max atteint\n      ELSE GREATEST(pick.next_required - p_xp_total, 0)\n    END AS xp_to_next\n  FROM pick;\n$function$\n"

p_source_version text DEFAULT NULL::text, p_metadata jsonb DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb)\n RETURNS json\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SECURITY DEFINER\n SET search_path TO 'pg_catalog', 'public'\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n    lock_h1 integer;\n    lock_h2 integer;\n    current_xp integer;\n    new_xp integer;\n    level_before_calc integer;\n    level_after_calc integer;\n    delta_applied integer;\n    delta_gap integer;\n    enhanced_metadata jsonb;\n    existing_event record;\n    new_event_id uuid;\nBEGIN\n    -- Validation idempotency_key\n    IF p_idempotency_key IS NULL OR length(p_idempotency_key) < 8 THEN\n        RAISE EXCEPTION 'invalid_idempotency_key';\n    END IF;\n\n    -- Validation delta\n    IF p_xp_delta = 0 THEN\n        RAISE EXCEPTION 'invalid_delta';\n    END IF;\n\n    -- Lock advisory\n    SELECT h1, h2 INTO lock_h1, lock_h2 FROM get_user_lock_keys(p_user_id);\n    \n    IF NOT pg_try_advisory_xact_lock(lock_h1, lock_h2) THEN\n        RAISE EXCEPTION 'lock_not_acquired';\n    END IF;\n\n    -- Lecture profile\n    SELECT xp INTO current_xp FROM profiles WHERE id = p_user_id FOR UPDATE;\n    \n    IF NOT FOUND THEN\n        RAISE EXCEPTION 'profile_not_found';\n    END IF;\n\n    -- Calculs\n    delta_applied := GREATEST(-current_xp, p_xp_delta);\n    new_xp := current_xp + delta_applied;\n    delta_gap := p_xp_delta - delta_applied;\n    \n    level_before_calc := compute_level(current_xp);\n    level_after_calc := compute_level(new_xp);\n\n    -- Mtadonnes\n    enhanced_metadata := COALESCE(p_metadata, '{}'::jsonb) || jsonb_build_object(\n        'source_ref', p_source_ref,\n        'requested_delta', p_xp_delta,\n        'applied_delta', delta_applied,\n        'gap', delta_gap\n    );\n\n    -- **AJOUT P8: Set GUC pour permettre l'INSERT dans xp_events**\n    PERFORM set_config('app.allow_xp_events_write','credit_xp', true);\n\n    -- Tentative insertion\n    INSERT INTO xp_events (\n        user_id, source_type, action_type, xp_delta, \n        xp_before, xp_after, level_before, level_after,\n        reference_id, metadata, idempotency_key,\n        source_id, source_version\n    ) VALUES (\n        p_user_id, 'api', 'credit_xp', delta_applied,\n        current_xp, new_xp, level_before_calc, level_after_calc,\n        p_reference_id, enhanced_metadata, p_idempotency_key,\n        p_source_ref, p_source_version\n    )\n    ON CONFLICT (idempotency_key) DO NOTHING\n    RETURNING id INTO new_event_id;\n\n    -- Gestion idempotence\n    IF new_event_id IS NULL THEN\n        SELECT * INTO existing_event FROM xp_events WHERE idempotency_key = p_idempotency_key;\n        \n        -- Validation conflit\n        IF existing_event.user_id != p_user_id OR \n           existing_event.metadata->>'source_ref' != p_source_ref OR\n           (existing_event.reference_id IS DISTINCT FROM p_reference_id) THEN\n            RAISE EXCEPTION 'conflict_mismatch';\n        END IF;\n\n        -- Retour event existant\n        RETURN json_build_object(\n            'event_id', existing_event.id,\n            'xp_before', existing_event.xp_before,\n            'xp_after', existing_event.xp_after,\n            'level_before', existing_event.level_before,\n            'level_after', existing_event.level_after,\n            'xp_delta_applied', existing_event.xp_delta,\n            'gap', (existing_event.metadata->>'gap')::integer,\n            'status', 'idempotent_return'\n        );\n    END IF;\n\n    -- Set GUC to allow profiles write\n    PERFORM set_config('app.allow_profiles_write','credit_xp', true);\n\n    -- Mise  jour profile\n    UPDATE profiles SET\n        xp = new_xp,\n        level = level_after_calc,\n        last_xp_event_at = now()\n    WHERE id = p_user_id;\n\n    -- Retour nouvel event\n    RETURN json_build_object(\n        'event_id', new_event_id,\n        'xp_before', current_xp,\n        'xp_after', new_xp,\n        'level_before', level_before_calc,\n        'level_after', level_after_calc,\n        'xp_delta_applied', delta_applied,\n        'gap', delta_gap,\n        'status', 'new_event_created'\n    );\nEND;\n$function$\n"

        {
            "args": "p_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now()",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "TABLE(source_id uuid, source_type text, action_type text, version integer, xp_value integer, cooldown_minutes integer, max_per_day integer, is_repeatable boolean, title text, description text, effective_from timestamp with time zone, effective_to timestamp with time zone)",
            "function": "get_active_xp_sources",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.get_active_xp_sources(p_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now())\n RETURNS TABLE(source_id uuid, source_type text, action_type text, version integer, xp_value integer, cooldown_minutes integer, max_per_day integer, is_repeatable boolean, title text, description text, effective_from timestamp with time zone, effective_to timestamp with time zone)\n LANGUAGE sql\n STABLE\nAS $function$\n  SELECT s.id, s.source_type, s.action_type, s.version, s.xp_value,\n         s.cooldown_minutes, s.max_per_day, s.is_repeatable,\n         s.title, s.description, s.effective_from, s.effective_to\n  FROM xp_sources s\n  WHERE s.is_active = true\n    AND (s.validity IS NULL OR p_at <@ s.validity)\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "user_id_param uuid, course_id_param uuid",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "TABLE(course_id uuid, total_lessons integer, completed_lessons integer, completion_percentage numeric)",
            "function": "get_user_course_progress",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.get_user_course_progress(user_id_param uuid, course_id_param uuid)\n RETURNS TABLE(course_id uuid, total_lessons integer, completed_lessons integer, completion_percentage numeric)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SECURITY DEFINER\n SET search_path TO 'pg_catalog', 'public'\nAS $function$\r\nBEGIN\r\n  RETURN QUERY\r\n  SELECT \r\n    c.id,\r\n    COUNT(l.id)::INTEGER as total_lessons,\r\n    COUNT(CASE WHEN up.status = 'completed' THEN 1 END)::INTEGER as completed_lessons,\r\n    ROUND(\r\n      (COUNT(CASE WHEN up.status = 'completed' THEN 1 END) * 100.0 / \r\n       NULLIF(COUNT(l.id), 0))::DECIMAL, 2\r\n    ) as completion_percentage\r\n  FROM courses c\r\n  JOIN modules m ON m.course_id = c.id\r\n  JOIN lessons l ON l.module_id = m.id\r\n  LEFT JOIN user_progress up ON up.lesson_id = l.id AND up.user_id = user_id_param\r\n  WHERE c.id = course_id_param\r\n  GROUP BY c.id;\r\nEND;\r\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "p_user_id uuid, p_lesson_id uuid",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "TABLE(h1 integer, h2 integer)",

            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.profiles_guard_write()\n RETURNS trigger\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SET search_path TO 'public', 'pg_temp'\nAS $function$\nDECLARE ctx text := current_setting('app.allow_profiles_write', true);\nBEGIN\n  IF ctx IS DISTINCT FROM 'credit_xp' THEN\n    RAISE EXCEPTION 'profiles writes must go through credit_xp (ctx=%)', COALESCE(ctx,'NULL');\n  END IF;\n  RETURN CASE WHEN TG_OP IN ('INSERT','UPDATE') THEN NEW ELSE OLD END;\nEND$function$\n"

        {
            "args": "p_achievement_key text, p_reason text DEFAULT 'Achievement removed'::text",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "TABLE(user_id uuid, xp_removed integer, new_total_xp integer, new_level integer)",
            "function": "recalculate_user_xp_after_achievement_removal",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.recalculate_user_xp_after_achievement_removal(p_achievement_key text, p_reason text DEFAULT 'Achievement removed'::text)\n RETURNS TABLE(user_id uuid, xp_removed integer, new_total_xp integer, new_level integer)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  user_record RECORD;\n  user_current_xp INTEGER;\n  user_current_level INTEGER;\n  xp_to_remove INTEGER;\n  new_xp INTEGER;\n  new_level INTEGER;\nBEGIN\n  -- Pour chaque utilisateur qui a des vnements XP de cet achievement\n  FOR user_record IN\n    SELECT \n      xe.user_id,\n      SUM(xe.xp_delta) as total_xp_to_remove\n    FROM xp_events xe\n    WHERE xe.source_type = 'achievement' \n      AND xe.action_type = 'unlock'\n      AND xe.metadata->>'achievement_key' = p_achievement_key\n      AND xe.xp_delta > 0  -- Seulement les gains XP positifs\n    GROUP BY xe.user_id\n  LOOP\n    -- Rcuprer les XP et niveau actuels de l'utilisateur\n    SELECT p.xp, p.level INTO user_current_xp, user_current_level \n    FROM profiles p \n    WHERE p.id = user_record.user_id;\n    \n    xp_to_remove := user_record.total_xp_to_remove;\n    new_xp := GREATEST(0, user_current_xp - xp_to_remove); -- Ne pas descendre sous 0\n    \n    -- Calculer le nouveau niveau\n    SELECT COALESCE(ld.level, 1)\n    INTO new_level\n    FROM level_definitions ld\n    WHERE ld.xp_required <= new_xp \n    ORDER BY ld.level DESC \n    LIMIT 1;\n    \n    -- Mettre  jour le profil utilisateur\n    UPDATE profiles \n    SET \n      xp = new_xp,\n      level = new_level,\n      updated_at = NOW()\n    WHERE id = user_record.user_id;\n    \n    -- Supprimer l'achievement de l'utilisateur (car l'achievement n'existe plus)\n    DELETE FROM user_achievements \n    WHERE user_id = user_record.user_id \n      AND achievement_type = p_achievement_key;\n    \n    -- Crer un vnement de correction pour traabilit\n    INSERT INTO xp_events (\n      user_id,\n      source_type,\n      action_type,\n      xp_delta,\n      xp_before,\n      xp_after,\n      level_before,\n      level_after,\n      metadata\n    ) VALUES (\n      user_record.user_id,\n      'admin',\n      'achievement_removal',\n      -xp_to_remove,\n      user_current_xp,\n      new_xp,\n      user_current_level,\n      new_level,\n      jsonb_build_object(\n        'reason', p_reason,\n        'removed_achievement', p_achievement_key,\n        'original_xp_reward', xp_to_remove,\n        'auto_correction', true,\n        'removal_date', NOW()\n      )\n    );\n    \n    -- Retourner les informations pour le log\n    user_id := user_record.user_id;\n    xp_removed := xp_to_remove;\n    new_total_xp := new_xp;\n    new_level := new_level;\n    RETURN NEXT;\n    \n    RAISE NOTICE 'Achievement XP corrected for user %: -% XP (% -> %), level % -> %', \n      user_record.user_id, xp_to_remove, user_current_xp, new_xp, user_current_level, new_level;\n      \n  END LOOP;\n  \n  RETURN;\nEND;\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "p_source_type text, p_action_type text, p_reason text DEFAULT 'Source removed'::text",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "TABLE(user_id uuid, xp_removed integer, new_total_xp integer, new_level integer)",
            "function": "recalculate_user_xp_after_source_removal",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.recalculate_user_xp_after_source_removal(p_source_type text, p_action_type text, p_reason text DEFAULT 'Source removed'::text)\n RETURNS TABLE(user_id uuid, xp_removed integer, new_total_xp integer, new_level integer)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  user_record RECORD;\n  user_current_xp INTEGER;\n  xp_to_remove INTEGER;\n  new_xp INTEGER;\n  new_level INTEGER;\nBEGIN\n  -- Pour chaque utilisateur qui a des vnements XP de cette source\n  FOR user_record IN\n    SELECT \n      xe.user_id,\n      SUM(xe.xp_delta) as total_xp_to_remove\n    FROM xp_events xe\n    WHERE xe.source_type = p_source_type \n      AND xe.action_type = p_action_type\n      AND xe.xp_delta > 0  -- Seulement les gains XP positifs\n    GROUP BY xe.user_id\n  LOOP\n    -- Rcuprer les XP actuels de l'utilisateur\n    SELECT p.xp INTO user_current_xp \n    FROM profiles p \n    WHERE p.id = user_record.user_id;\n    \n    xp_to_remove := user_record.total_xp_to_remove;\n    new_xp := GREATEST(0, user_current_xp - xp_to_remove); -- Ne pas descendre sous 0\n    \n    -- Calculer le nouveau niveau\n    SELECT COALESCE(ld.level, 1)\n    INTO new_level\n    FROM level_definitions ld\n    WHERE ld.xp_required <= new_xp \n    ORDER BY ld.level DESC \n    LIMIT 1;\n    \n    -- Mettre  jour le profil utilisateur\n    UPDATE profiles \n    SET \n      xp = new_xp,\n      level = new_level,\n      updated_at = NOW()\n    WHERE id = user_record.user_id;\n    \n    -- Crer un vnement de correction pour traabilit\n    INSERT INTO xp_events (\n      user_id,\n      source_type,\n      action_type,\n      xp_delta,\n      xp_before,\n      xp_after,\n      level_before,\n      level_after,\n      metadata\n    ) VALUES (\n      user_record.user_id,\n      'admin',\n      'source_removal',\n      -xp_to_remove,\n      user_current_xp,\n      new_xp,\n      (SELECT level FROM profiles WHERE id = user_record.user_id),\n      new_level,\n      jsonb_build_object(\n        'reason', p_reason,\n        'removed_source', p_source_type || ':' || p_action_type,\n        'original_xp_events_removed', xp_to_remove,\n        'auto_correction', true,\n        'removal_date', NOW()\n      )\n    );\n    \n    -- Retourner les informations pour le log\n    user_id := user_record.user_id;\n    xp_removed := xp_to_remove;\n    new_total_xp := new_xp;\n    new_level := new_level;\n    RETURN NEXT;\n    \n    RAISE NOTICE 'XP corrected for user %: -% XP (% -> %), level %', \n      user_record.user_id, xp_to_remove, user_current_xp, new_xp, new_level;\n      \n  END LOOP;\n  \n  RETURN;\nEND;\n$function$\n"
        },

            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.set_updated_at()\n RETURNS trigger\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nBEGIN\n  -- Vrifier si des colonnes autres qu'updated_at ont chang\n  -- vite write amplification : ne met  jour updated_at que si ncessaire\n  IF OLD IS DISTINCT FROM NEW THEN\n    NEW.updated_at = now();\n  END IF;\n  \n  RETURN NEW;\nEND;\n$function$\n"

        {
            "args": "target_user_id uuid, session_ip inet DEFAULT NULL::inet, session_user_agent text DEFAULT NULL::text",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "uuid",
            "function": "start_user_session",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.start_user_session(target_user_id uuid, session_ip inet DEFAULT NULL::inet, session_user_agent text DEFAULT NULL::text)\n RETURNS uuid\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SECURITY DEFINER\n SET search_path TO 'pg_catalog', 'public'\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  session_id UUID;\n  last_session RECORD;\nBEGIN\n  -- Vrifier la dernire session pour calculer les streaks\n  SELECT * FROM user_login_sessions \n  WHERE user_id = target_user_id \n  ORDER BY session_start DESC \n  LIMIT 1 INTO last_session;\n  \n  -- Crer une nouvelle session\n  INSERT INTO user_login_sessions (user_id, ip_address, user_agent)\n  VALUES (target_user_id, session_ip, session_user_agent)\n  RETURNING id INTO session_id;\n  \n  -- Mettre  jour le streak si ncessaire (via StreakService)\n  -- Cela dclenchera automatiquement la vrification des achievements\n  \n  RETURN session_id;\nEND;\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "target_user_id uuid DEFAULT NULL::uuid",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "TABLE(user_id uuid, achievement_key text, xp_corrected integer, sync_status text)",
            "function": "sync_achievement_xp",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.sync_achievement_xp(target_user_id uuid DEFAULT NULL::uuid)\n RETURNS TABLE(user_id uuid, achievement_key text, xp_corrected integer, sync_status text)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  user_record RECORD;\n  achievement_record RECORD;\n  missing_xp INTEGER;\n  user_current_xp INTEGER;\n  new_user_xp INTEGER;\nBEGIN\n  -- Si aucun user spcifi, traiter tous les users\n  FOR user_record IN \n    SELECT DISTINCT ua.user_id\n    FROM user_achievements ua\n    WHERE (target_user_id IS NULL OR ua.user_id = target_user_id)\n  LOOP\n    -- Pour chaque user, vrifier ses achievements vs ses XP events\n    FOR achievement_record IN\n      SELECT \n        ua.user_id,\n        ua.achievement_type,\n        ua.unlocked_at,\n        ad.xp_reward,\n        ad.title,\n        CASE \n          WHEN EXISTS (\n            SELECT 1 FROM xp_events xe \n            WHERE xe.user_id = ua.user_id \n              AND xe.source_type = 'achievement' \n              AND xe.action_type = 'unlock'\n              AND xe.metadata->>'achievement_key' = ua.achievement_type\n          ) THEN FALSE\n          ELSE TRUE\n        END as missing_xp_event\n      FROM user_achievements ua\n      JOIN achievement_definitions ad ON ua.achievement_type = ad.achievement_key\n      WHERE ua.user_id = user_record.user_id\n        AND ad.is_active = true\n    LOOP\n      \n      -- Si l'vnement XP manque, le crer\n      IF achievement_record.missing_xp_event THEN\n        -- Rcuprer les XP actuels de l'utilisateur\n        SELECT p.xp INTO user_current_xp \n        FROM profiles p \n        WHERE p.id = achievement_record.user_id;\n        \n        new_user_xp := user_current_xp + achievement_record.xp_reward;\n        \n        -- Crer l'vnement XP manquant\n        INSERT INTO xp_events (\n          user_id,\n          source_type,\n          action_type,\n          xp_delta,\n          xp_before,\n          xp_after,\n          level_before,\n          level_after,\n          metadata,\n          created_at\n        ) VALUES (\n          achievement_record.user_id,\n          'achievement',\n          'unlock',\n          achievement_record.xp_reward,\n          user_current_xp,\n          new_user_xp,\n          (SELECT level FROM profiles WHERE id = achievement_record.user_id),\n          (SELECT level FROM level_definitions WHERE xp_required <= new_user_xp ORDER BY level DESC LIMIT 1),\n          jsonb_build_object(\n            'source', 'achievement:unlock',\n            'achievement_key', achievement_record.achievement_type,\n            'achievement_name', achievement_record.title,\n            'auto_sync', true,\n            'sync_date', NOW()\n          ),\n          achievement_record.unlocked_at\n        );\n        \n        -- Mettre  jour les XP du profil\n        UPDATE profiles \n        SET xp = new_user_xp,\n            level = (SELECT level FROM level_definitions WHERE xp_required <= new_user_xp ORDER BY level DESC LIMIT 1)\n        WHERE id = achievement_record.user_id;\n        \n        -- Retourner le rsultat\n        user_id := achievement_record.user_id;\n        achievement_key := achievement_record.achievement_type;\n        xp_corrected := achievement_record.xp_reward;\n        sync_status := 'XP_ADDED';\n        RETURN NEXT;\n      END IF;\n      \n    END LOOP;\n  END LOOP;\n  \n  RETURN;\nEND;\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "",

            "function": "sync_user_admin_claims",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.sync_user_admin_claims()\n RETURNS trigger\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SECURITY DEFINER\n SET search_path TO 'pg_catalog', 'public'\nAS $function$\r\nBEGIN\r\n    -- Mettre  jour les claims JWT quand is_admin change\r\n    IF NEW.is_admin IS DISTINCT FROM OLD.is_admin THEN\r\n        -- Log le changement pour debugging\r\n        RAISE NOTICE 'Admin status changed for user %: % -> %', NEW.id, OLD.is_admin, NEW.is_admin;\r\n    END IF;\r\n    \r\n    RETURN NEW;\r\nEND;\r\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "TABLE(session_id integer, operation_order integer, event_id uuid, success boolean, xp_before integer, xp_after integer, error_message text)",
            "function": "test_concurrent_credit_xp",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.test_concurrent_credit_xp()\n RETURNS TABLE(session_id integer, operation_order integer, event_id uuid, success boolean, xp_before integer, xp_after integer, error_message text)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  result JSONB;\n  initial_xp INTEGER;\n  final_xp INTEGER;\nBEGIN\n  -- Get initial XP\n  SELECT profiles.xp INTO initial_xp FROM profiles WHERE id = '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001';\n  \n  FOR session_id IN 1..5 LOOP\n    BEGIN\n      -- Each \"session\" tries to credit the same XP with same idempotency key\n      SELECT credit_xp(\n        '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',\n        'lesson:completion',\n        100,\n        'concurrent-test-key-1',  -- Same key for all attempts\n        'lesson-p10-001',\n        '1',\n        jsonb_build_object('session', session_id, 'test', 'concurrency')\n      ) INTO result;\n      \n      -- Get final XP\n      SELECT profiles.xp INTO final_xp FROM profiles WHERE id = '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001';\n      \n      RETURN QUERY SELECT \n        session_id,\n        session_id,\n        (result->>'event_id')::UUID,\n        TRUE,\n        initial_xp,\n        final_xp,\n        NULL::TEXT;\n        \n    EXCEPTION WHEN OTHERS THEN\n      RETURN QUERY SELECT \n        session_id,\n        session_id,\n        NULL::UUID,\n        FALSE,\n        initial_xp,\n        0,\n        SQLERRM;\n    END;\n  END LOOP;\nEND;\n$function$\n"

        {
            "args": "",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "trigger",
            "function": "trg_level_defs_monotonic",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.trg_level_defs_monotonic()\n RETURNS trigger\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  prev_req integer;\n  next_req integer;\nBEGIN\n  -- Rcuprer les valeurs prcdentes/suivantes par niveau\n  SELECT xp_required INTO prev_req\n  FROM level_definitions WHERE level = NEW.level - 1;\n  \n  SELECT xp_required INTO next_req\n  FROM level_definitions WHERE level = NEW.level + 1;\n\n  -- Vrifier monotonie stricte avec voisins existants\n  IF prev_req IS NOT NULL AND NOT (prev_req < NEW.xp_required) THEN\n     RAISE EXCEPTION 'Monotony violation: xp_required(%) must be > previous(%)', NEW.xp_required, prev_req;\n  END IF;\n  \n  IF next_req IS NOT NULL AND NOT (NEW.xp_required < next_req) THEN\n     RAISE EXCEPTION 'Monotony violation: xp_required(%) must be < next(%)', NEW.xp_required, next_req;\n  END IF;\n\n  -- Level 1 doit rester  0 (contrat systme)\n  IF NEW.level = 1 AND NEW.xp_required != 0 THEN\n     RAISE EXCEPTION 'Level 1 must have xp_required = 0';\n  END IF;\n\n  RETURN NEW;\nEND;\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "",
            "schema": "public",
            "returns": "trigger",
            "function": "trigger_achievement_check",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.trigger_achievement_check()\n RETURNS trigger\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  result RECORD;\nBEGIN\n  -- Vrifier les achievements aprs toute modification XP/streak/level\n  IF TG_TABLE_NAME = 'xp_events' AND TG_OP = 'INSERT' THEN\n    SELECT * FROM check_and_unlock_achievements(NEW.user_id) INTO result;\n  ELSIF TG_TABLE_NAME = 'profiles' AND TG_OP = 'UPDATE' THEN\n    SELECT * FROM check_and_unlock_achievements(NEW.id) INTO result;\n  ELSIF TG_TABLE_NAME = 'user_xp_balance' AND TG_OP IN ('INSERT', 'UPDATE') THEN\n    SELECT * FROM check_and_unlock_achievements(NEW.user_id) INTO result;\n  END IF;\n  \n  -- Log si des achievements ont t dbloqus\n  IF result.unlocked_count > 0 THEN\n    RAISE NOTICE 'Unlocked % achievements for user %', result.unlocked_count, COALESCE(NEW.user_id, NEW.id);\n  END IF;\n  \n  RETURN COALESCE(NEW, OLD);\nEND;\n$function$\n"
        },
        {

            "function": "unlock_achievement",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.unlock_achievement(p_user_id uuid, p_code text, p_version integer, p_idempotency_key text, p_scope text DEFAULT NULL::text, p_reference_id uuid DEFAULT NULL::uuid)\n RETURNS TABLE(ua_id uuid, event_id uuid, xp_before integer, xp_after integer, level_before integer, level_after integer)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SECURITY DEFINER\n SET search_path TO 'pg_catalog', 'public'\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  v_achievement_def RECORD;\n  v_profile RECORD;\n  v_existing_achievement uuid;\n  v_new_ua_id uuid;\n  v_new_event_id uuid;\n  v_previous_xp int;\n  v_new_xp int;\n  v_previous_level int;\n  v_new_level int;\n  v_level_def RECORD;\n  v_progress_current int;\n  v_progress_target int;\n  v_is_unlocked boolean := false;\nBEGIN\n  -- 1. Validation paramtres\n  IF p_user_id IS NULL OR p_code IS NULL OR p_version IS NULL OR p_idempotency_key IS NULL THEN\n    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Paramtres obligatoires manquants';\n  END IF;\n\n  -- 2. Vrifier achievement_definition\n  SELECT * INTO v_achievement_def \n  FROM public.achievement_definitions \n  WHERE code = p_code AND version = p_version AND is_active = true;\n  \n  IF NOT FOUND THEN\n    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Achievement non trouv: % v%', p_code, p_version;\n  END IF;\n\n  -- 3. Rcuprer profil utilisateur\n  SELECT * INTO v_profile \n  FROM public.profiles \n  WHERE id = p_user_id;\n  \n  IF NOT FOUND THEN\n    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Profil utilisateur non trouv: %', p_user_id;\n  END IF;\n\n  -- 4. Vrifier si dj unlocked (idempotence)\n  -- CORRECTION: utiliser achievement_type au lieu de achievement_code\n  SELECT ua.id INTO v_existing_achievement\n  FROM public.user_achievements ua\n  WHERE ua.user_id = p_user_id \n    AND ua.achievement_type = p_code \n    AND ua.achievement_version = p_version\n    AND ua.details->>'idempotency_key' = p_idempotency_key;\n\n  IF FOUND THEN\n    -- Retourner l'existing sans modifications\n    SELECT ua.id, xe.id, xe.xp_before, xe.xp_after, xe.level_before, xe.level_after\n    INTO ua_id, event_id, xp_before, xp_after, level_before, level_after\n    FROM public.user_achievements ua\n    LEFT JOIN public.xp_events xe ON xe.user_id = ua.user_id \n      AND xe.metadata->>'achievement_code' = ua.achievement_type\n      AND xe.metadata->>'idempotency_key' = p_idempotency_key\n    WHERE ua.id = v_existing_achievement;\n    RETURN NEXT;\n    RETURN;\n  END IF;\n\n  -- 5. Vrifier conditions selon condition_type\n  CASE v_achievement_def.condition_type\n    WHEN 'xp_threshold' THEN\n      v_progress_target := (v_achievement_def.condition_params->>'threshold')::int;\n      v_progress_current := COALESCE(v_profile.xp, 0);\n      v_is_unlocked := v_progress_current >= v_progress_target;\n      \n    WHEN 'level_reached' THEN\n      v_progress_target := (v_achievement_def.condition_params->>'level')::int;\n      v_progress_current := COALESCE(v_profile.level, 1);\n      v_is_unlocked := v_progress_current >= v_progress_target;\n      \n    WHEN 'lesson_count' THEN\n      v_progress_target := (v_achievement_def.condition_params->>'count')::int;\n      -- Compter les leons compltes par l'utilisateur (utiliser la bonne table)\n      SELECT COUNT(*) INTO v_progress_current\n      FROM public.user_progress \n      WHERE user_id = p_user_id AND (status = 'completed' OR completed_at IS NOT NULL);\n      v_is_unlocked := v_progress_current >= v_progress_target;\n      \n    WHEN 'profile_completion' THEN\n      v_progress_target := (v_achievement_def.condition_params->>'percentage')::int;\n      -- Calcul simple profile completion (4 champs principaux)\n      v_progress_current := (\n        CASE WHEN v_profile.first_name IS NOT NULL AND v_profile.first_name != '' THEN 25 ELSE 0 END +\n        CASE WHEN v_profile.last_name IS NOT NULL AND v_profile.last_name != '' THEN 25 ELSE 0 END +\n        CASE WHEN v_profile.avatar_url IS NOT NULL AND v_profile.avatar_url != '' THEN 25 ELSE 0 END +\n        CASE WHEN v_profile.bio IS NOT NULL AND v_profile.bio != '' THEN 25 ELSE 0 END\n      );\n      v_is_unlocked := v_progress_current >= v_progress_target;\n      \n    WHEN 'course_completion' THEN\n      -- Vrifier completion d'un cours spcifique\n      IF p_scope IS NULL OR p_reference_id IS NULL THEN\n        RAISE EXCEPTION 'Scope et reference_id requis pour course_completion';\n      END IF;\n      \n      SELECT EXISTS(\n        SELECT 1 FROM public.user_course_progress \n        WHERE user_id = p_user_id \n          AND course_id = p_reference_id \n          AND completion_percentage = 100\n      ) INTO v_is_unlocked;\n      \n    ELSE\n      RAISE EXCEPTION 'Type de condition non support: %', v_achievement_def.condition_type;\n  END CASE;\n\n  -- 6. Si conditions non remplies, arrter\n  IF NOT v_is_unlocked THEN\n    RAISE EXCEPTION 'Conditions achievement non remplies. Progress: %/% pour %', \n      v_progress_current, v_progress_target, v_achievement_def.condition_type;\n  END IF;\n\n  -- 7. Capturer tat XP/niveau avant\n  v_previous_xp := COALESCE(v_profile.xp, 0);\n  v_previous_level := COALESCE(v_profile.level, 1);\n\n  -- **AJOUT P8: Set GUC pour permettre l'INSERT dans user_achievements**\n  PERFORM set_config('app.allow_user_achievements_write','unlock_achievement', true);\n\n  -- 8. Crer user_achievement\n  -- CORRECTION: utiliser achievement_type, achievement_id, et stocker idempotency_key dans details\n  INSERT INTO public.user_achievements (\n    user_id, \n    achievement_type, \n    achievement_name,\n    xp_reward,\n    achievement_id, \n    achievement_version, \n    scope,\n    details,\n    unlocked_at\n  ) VALUES (\n    p_user_id, \n    p_code,\n    v_achievement_def.title,\n    v_achievement_def.xp_reward,\n    v_achievement_def.id, \n    p_version,\n    p_scope,\n    jsonb_build_object(\n      'idempotency_key', p_idempotency_key,\n      'reference_id', p_reference_id,\n      'progress_at_unlock', v_progress_current\n    ),\n    NOW()\n  ) RETURNING id INTO v_new_ua_id;\n\n  -- 9. Award XP si dfini\n  IF v_achievement_def.xp_reward > 0 THEN\n    v_new_xp := v_previous_xp + v_achievement_def.xp_reward;\n    \n    -- Calculer nouveau niveau\n    SELECT level INTO v_new_level\n    FROM public.level_definitions\n    WHERE xp_required <= v_new_xp\n    ORDER BY xp_required DESC\n    LIMIT 1;\n    \n    IF v_new_level IS NULL THEN\n      v_new_level := 1;\n    END IF;\n\n    -- **AJOUT P8: Set GUC pour permettre l'UPDATE dans profiles**\n    PERFORM set_config('app.allow_profiles_write','unlock_achievement', true);\n\n    -- Mettre  jour profiles\n    UPDATE public.profiles \n    SET \n      xp = v_new_xp,\n      level = v_new_level,\n      last_xp_event_at = NOW()\n    WHERE id = p_user_id;\n\n    -- **AJOUT P8: Set GUC pour permettre l'INSERT dans xp_events**\n    PERFORM set_config('app.allow_xp_events_write','unlock_achievement', true);\n\n    -- Crer xp_event\n    INSERT INTO public.xp_events (\n      user_id, source_type, action_type, \n      xp_delta, xp_before, xp_after,\n      level_before, level_after,\n      metadata\n    ) VALUES (\n      p_user_id, 'achievement', 'unlock',\n      v_achievement_def.xp_reward, v_previous_xp, v_new_xp,\n      v_previous_level, v_new_level,\n      jsonb_build_object(\n        'achievement_code', p_code,\n        'achievement_version', p_version,\n        'achievement_title', v_achievement_def.title,\n        'idempotency_key', p_idempotency_key\n      )\n    ) RETURNING id INTO v_new_event_id;\n  ELSE\n    -- Pas de XP reward\n    v_new_xp := v_previous_xp;\n    v_new_level := v_previous_level;\n    v_new_event_id := NULL;\n  END IF;\n\n  -- 10. Retourner rsultats\n  ua_id := v_new_ua_id;\n  event_id := v_new_event_id;\n  xp_before := v_previous_xp;\n  xp_after := v_new_xp;\n  level_before := v_previous_level;\n  level_after := v_new_level;\n  \n  RETURN NEXT;\nEND;\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "p_user_id uuid, p_code text, p_version integer, p_idempotency_key text, p_scope text DEFAULT NULL::text, p_reference_id uuid DEFAULT NULL::uuid",

            "returns": "TABLE(ua_id uuid, event_id uuid, xp_before integer, xp_after integer, level_before integer, level_after integer)",
            "function": "unlock_achievement_safe",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.unlock_achievement_safe(p_user_id uuid, p_code text, p_version integer, p_idempotency_key text, p_scope text DEFAULT NULL::text, p_reference_id uuid DEFAULT NULL::uuid)\n RETURNS TABLE(ua_id uuid, event_id uuid, xp_before integer, xp_after integer, level_before integer, level_after integer)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nBEGIN\n  -- Contrle: admin OU utilisateur agit sur lui-mme\n  IF NOT public.is_admin() AND auth.uid() IS DISTINCT FROM p_user_id THEN\n    RAISE EXCEPTION 'not allowed: cannot unlock achievement for other users';\n  END IF;\n  \n  -- Appel fonction scurise avec RETURN QUERY\n  RETURN QUERY \n  SELECT * FROM public.unlock_achievement(p_user_id, p_code, p_version, p_idempotency_key, p_scope, p_reference_id);\nEND $function$\n"

            "function": "update_user_profile",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.update_user_profile(p_user_id uuid, p_profile_data jsonb)\n RETURNS TABLE(id uuid, email character varying, full_name text, avatar_url text, phone text, profession text, company text, level integer, xp integer, current_streak integer, is_admin boolean, last_completed_at timestamp with time zone, created_at timestamp with time zone, updated_at timestamp with time zone)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SECURITY DEFINER\n SET search_path TO 'pg_catalog', 'public'\nAS $function$\r\n  BEGIN\r\n    -- Mettre  jour le profil\r\n    UPDATE profiles\r\n    SET\r\n      full_name = COALESCE(p_profile_data->>'full_name', profiles.full_name),\r\n      avatar_url = COALESCE(p_profile_data->>'avatar_url', profiles.avatar_url),\r\n      phone = COALESCE(p_profile_data->>'phone', profiles.phone),\r\n      profession = COALESCE(p_profile_data->>'profession', profiles.profession),\r\n      company = COALESCE(p_profile_data->>'company', profiles.company),\r\n      updated_at = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP\r\n    WHERE profiles.id = p_user_id;\r\n\r\n    -- Retourner le profil mis  jour\r\n    RETURN QUERY\r\n    SELECT\r\n      prof.id,\r\n      u.email,\r\n      prof.full_name,\r\n      prof.avatar_url,\r\n      prof.phone,\r\n      prof.profession,\r\n      prof.company,\r\n      prof.level,\r\n      prof.xp,\r\n      prof.current_streak,\r\n      prof.is_admin,\r\n      prof.last_completed_at,\r\n      prof.created_at,\r\n      prof.updated_at\r\n    FROM profiles prof\r\n    JOIN auth.users u ON u.id = prof.id\r\n    WHERE prof.id = p_user_id;\r\n  END;\r\n  $function$\n"

            "function": "update_user_settings",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.update_user_settings(settings_data jsonb, user_id uuid DEFAULT auth.uid())\n RETURNS TABLE(notification_settings jsonb, privacy_settings jsonb, learning_preferences jsonb)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\r\nBEGIN\r\n  RETURN QUERY\r\n  INSERT INTO user_settings(user_id, notification_settings, privacy_settings, learning_preferences)\r\n  VALUES (\r\n    user_id,\r\n    COALESCE(settings_data->'notification_settings', '{}'::jsonb),\r\n    COALESCE(settings_data->'privacy_settings', '{}'::jsonb),\r\n    COALESCE(settings_data->'learning_preferences', '{}'::jsonb)\r\n  )\r\n  ON CONFLICT (user_id) DO UPDATE\r\n    SET notification_settings = COALESCE(settings_data->'notification_settings', user_settings.notification_settings),\r\n        privacy_settings = COALESCE(settings_data->'privacy_settings', user_settings.privacy_settings),\r\n        learning_preferences = COALESCE(settings_data->'learning_preferences', user_settings.learning_preferences),\r\n        updated_at = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP\r\n  RETURNING\r\n    user_settings.notification_settings AS notification_settings,\r\n    user_settings.privacy_settings AS privacy_settings,\r\n    user_settings.learning_preferences AS learning_preferences;\r\nEND;\r\n$function$\n"

)::realtime.wal_rls;\n\n    else\n        output = jsonb_build_object(\n            'schema', wal ->> 'schema',\n            'table', wal ->> 'table',\n            'type', action,\n refer to valid columns that the claimed role may access\n    - values are coercable to the correct column type\n    */\n    declare\n        col_names text[] = coalesce(\n                array_agg(c.column_name order by c.ordinal_position),\n                '{}'::text[]\n            )\n            from\n                information_schema.columns c\n            where\n                format('%I.%I', c.table_schema, c.table_name)::regclass = new.entity\n                and pg_catalog.has_column_privilege(\n                    (new.claims ->> 'role'),\n                    format('%I.%I', c.table_schema, c.table_name)::regclass,\n                    c.column_name,\n                    'SELECT'\n                );\n        filter realtime.user_defined_filter;\n        col_type regtype;\n\n        in_val jsonb;\n    begin\n        for filter in select * from unnest(new.filters) loop\n            -- Filtered column is valid\n            if not filter.column_name = any(col_names) then\n                raise exception 'invalid column for filter %', filter.column_name;\n            end if;\n\n            -- Type is sanitized and safe for string interpolation\n            col_type = (\n                select atttypid::regtype\n                from pg_catalog.pg_attribute\n                where attrelid = new.entity\n                      and attname = filter.column_name\n            );\n            if col_type is null then\n                raise exception 'failed to lookup type for column %', filter.column_name;\n            end if;\n\n            -- Set maximum number of entries for in filter\n            if filter.op = 'in'::realtime.equality_op then\n                in_val = realtime.cast(filter.value, (col_type::text || '[]')::regtype);\n                if coalesce(jsonb_array_length(in_val), 0) > 100 then\n                    raise exception 'too many values for `in` filter.             "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION storage.get_size_by_bucket()\n RETURNS TABLE(size bigint, bucket_id text)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nBEGIN\n    return query\n        select sum((metadata->>'size')::int) as size, obj.bucket_id\n        from \"storage\".objects as obj\n        group by obj.bucket_id;\nEND\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "bucket_id text, prefix_param text, delimiter_param text, max_keys integer DEFAULT 100, next_key_token text DEFAULT ''::text, next_upload_token text DEFAULT ''::text",
            "schema": "storage",
            "returns": "TABLE(key text, id text, created_at timestamp with time zone)",
            "function": "list_multipart_uploads_with_delimiter",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION storage.list_multipart_uploads_with_delimiter(bucket_id text, prefix_param text, delimiter_param text, max_keys integer DEFAULT 100, next_key_token text DEFAULT ''::text, next_upload_token text DEFAULT ''::text)\n RETURNS TABLE(key text, id text, created_at timestamp with time zone)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nBEGIN\n    RETURN QUERY EXECUTE\n        'SELECT DISTINCT ON(key COLLATE \"C\") * from (\n            SELECT\n                CASE\n                    WHEN position($2 IN substring(key from length($1) + 1)) > 0 THEN\n                        substring(key from 1 for length($1) + position($2 IN substring(key from length($1) + 1)))\n                    ELSE\n                        key\n                END AS key, id, created_at\n            FROM\n                storage.s3_multipart_uploads\n            WHERE\n                bucket_id = $5 AND\n                key ILIKE $1 || ''%'' AND\n                CASE\n                    WHEN $4 != '''' AND $6 = '''' THEN\n                        CASE\n                            WHEN position($2 IN substring(key from length($1) + 1)) > 0 THEN\n                                substring(key from 1 for length($1) + position($2 IN substring(key from length($1) + 1))) COLLATE \"C\" > $4\n                            ELSE\n                                key COLLATE \"C\" > $4\n                            END\n                    ELSE\n                        true\n                END AND\n                CASE\n                    WHEN $6 != '''' THEN\n                        id COLLATE \"C\" > $6\n                    ELSE\n                        true\n                    END\n            ORDER BY\n                key COLLATE \"C\" ASC, created_at ASC) as e order by key COLLATE \"C\" LIMIT $3'\n        USING prefix_param, delimiter_param, max_keys, next_key_token, bucket_id, next_upload_token;\nEND;\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "bucket_id text, prefix_param text, delimiter_param text, max_keys integer DEFAULT 100, start_after text DEFAULT ''::text, next_token text DEFAULT ''::text",
            "schema": "storage",
            "returns": "TABLE(name text, id uuid, metadata jsonb, updated_at timestamp with time zone)",
            "function": "list_objects_with_delimiter",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION storage.list_objects_with_delimiter(bucket_id text, prefix_param text, delimiter_param text, max_keys integer DEFAULT 100, start_after text DEFAULT ''::text, next_token text DEFAULT ''::text)\n RETURNS TABLE(name text, id uuid, metadata jsonb, updated_at timestamp with time zone)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\nAS $function$\nBEGIN\n    RETURN QUERY EXECUTE\n        'SELECT DISTINCT ON(name COLLATE \"C\") * from (\n            SELECT\n                CASE\n                    WHEN position($2 IN substring(name from length($1) + 1)) > 0 THEN\n                        substring(name from 1 for length($1) + position($2 IN substring(name from length($1) + 1)))\n                    ELSE\n                        name\n                END AS name, id, metadata, updated_at\n            FROM\n                storage.objects\n            WHERE\n                bucket_id = $5 AND\n                name ILIKE $1 || ''%'' AND\n                CASE\n                    WHEN $6 != '''' THEN\n                    name COLLATE \"C\" > $6\n                ELSE true END\n                AND CASE\n                    WHEN $4 != '''' THEN\n                        CASE\n                            WHEN position($2 IN substring(name from length($1) + 1)) > 0 THEN\n                                substring(name from 1 for length($1) + position($2 IN substring(name from length($1) + 1))) COLLATE \"C\" > $4\n                            ELSE\n                                name COLLATE \"C\" > $4\n                            END\n                    ELSE\n                        true\n                END\n            ORDER BY\n                name COLLATE \"C\" ASC) as e order by name COLLATE \"C\" LIMIT $3'\n        USING prefix_param, delimiter_param, max_keys, next_token, bucket_id, start_after;\nEND;\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "",
            "schema": "storage",

            "function": "operation",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION storage.operation()\n RETURNS text\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n STABLE\nAS $function$\nBEGIN\n    RETURN current_setting('storage.operation', true);\nEND;\n$function$\n"

        {
            "args": "prefix text, bucketname text, limits integer DEFAULT 100, levels integer DEFAULT 1, offsets integer DEFAULT 0, search text DEFAULT ''::text, sortcolumn text DEFAULT 'name'::text, sortorder text DEFAULT 'asc'::text",
            "schema": "storage",
            "returns": "TABLE(name text, id uuid, updated_at timestamp with time zone, created_at timestamp with time zone, last_accessed_at timestamp with time zone, metadata jsonb)",
            "function": "search",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION storage.search(prefix text, bucketname text, limits integer DEFAULT 100, levels integer DEFAULT 1, offsets integer DEFAULT 0, search text DEFAULT ''::text, sortcolumn text DEFAULT 'name'::text, sortorder text DEFAULT 'asc'::text)\n RETURNS TABLE(name text, id uuid, updated_at timestamp with time zone, created_at timestamp with time zone, last_accessed_at timestamp with time zone, metadata jsonb)\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n STABLE\nAS $function$\ndeclare\n  v_order_by text;\n  v_sort_order text;\nbegin\n  case\n    when sortcolumn = 'name' then\n      v_order_by = 'name';\n    when sortcolumn = 'updated_at' then\n      v_order_by = 'updated_at';\n    when sortcolumn = 'created_at' then\n      v_order_by = 'created_at';\n    when sortcolumn = 'last_accessed_at' then\n      v_order_by = 'last_accessed_at';\n    else\n      v_order_by = 'name';\n  end case;\n\n  case\n    when sortorder = 'asc' then\n      v_sort_order = 'asc';\n    when sortorder = 'desc' then\n      v_sort_order = 'desc';\n    else\n      v_sort_order = 'asc';\n  end case;\n\n  v_order_by = v_order_by || ' ' || v_sort_order;\n\n  return query execute\n    'with folders as (\n       select path_tokens[$1] as folder\n       from storage.objects\n         where objects.name ilike $2 || $3 || ''%''\n           and bucket_id = $4\n           and array_length(objects.path_tokens, 1) <> $1\n       group by folder\n       order by folder ' || v_sort_order || '\n     )\n     (select folder as \"name\",\n            null as id,\n            null as updated_at,\n            null as created_at,\n            null as last_accessed_at,\n            null as metadata from folders)\n     union all\n     (select path_tokens[$1] as \"name\",\n            id,\n            updated_at,\n            created_at,\n            last_accessed_at,\n            metadata\n     from storage.objects\n     where objects.name ilike $2 || $3 || ''%''\n       and bucket_id = $4\n       and array_length(objects.path_tokens, 1) = $1\n     order by ' || v_order_by || ')\n     limit $5\n     offset $6' using levels, prefix, search, bucketname, limits, offsets;\nend;\n$function$\n"
        },

            "args": "",
            "schema": "supabase_functions",
            "returns": "trigger",
            "function": "http_request",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION supabase_functions.http_request()\n RETURNS trigger\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SECURITY DEFINER\n SET search_path TO 'supabase_functions'\nAS $function$\n    DECLARE\n      request_id bigint;\n      payload jsonb;\n      url text := TG_ARGV[0]::text;\n      method text := TG_ARGV[1]::text;\n      headers jsonb DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb;\n      params jsonb DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb;\n      timeout_ms integer DEFAULT 1000;\n    BEGIN\n      IF url IS NULL OR url = 'null' THEN\n        RAISE EXCEPTION 'url argument is missing';\n      END IF;\n\n      IF method IS NULL OR method = 'null' THEN\n        RAISE EXCEPTION 'method argument is missing';\n      END IF;\n\n      IF TG_ARGV[2] IS NULL OR TG_ARGV[2] = 'null' THEN\n        headers = '{\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}'::jsonb;\n      ELSE\n        headers = TG_ARGV[2]::jsonb;\n      END IF;\n\n      IF TG_ARGV[3] IS NULL OR TG_ARGV[3] = 'null' THEN\n        params = '{}'::jsonb;\n      ELSE\n        params = TG_ARGV[3]::jsonb;\n      END IF;\n\n      IF TG_ARGV[4] IS NULL OR TG_ARGV[4] = 'null' THEN\n        timeout_ms = 1000;\n      ELSE\n        timeout_ms = TG_ARGV[4]::integer;\n      END IF;\n\n      CASE\n        WHEN method = 'GET' THEN\n          SELECT http_get INTO request_id FROM net.http_get(\n            url,\n            params,\n            headers,\n            timeout_ms\n          );\n        WHEN method = 'POST' THEN\n          payload = jsonb_build_object(\n            'old_record', OLD,\n            'record', NEW,\n            'type', TG_OP,\n            'table', TG_TABLE_NAME,\n            'schema', TG_TABLE_SCHEMA\n          );\n\n          SELECT http_post INTO request_id FROM net.http_post(\n            url,\n            payload,\n            params,\n            headers,\n            timeout_ms\n          );\n        ELSE\n          RAISE EXCEPTION 'method argument % is invalid', method;\n      END CASE;\n\n      INSERT INTO supabase_functions.hooks\n        (hook_table_id, hook_name, request_id)\n      VALUES\n        (TG_RELID, TG_NAME, request_id);\n\n      RETURN NEW;\n    END\n  $function$\n"
        },

        {
            "args": "new_secret text, new_name text DEFAULT NULL::text, new_description text DEFAULT ''::text, new_key_id uuid DEFAULT NULL::uuid",
            "schema": "vault",
            "returns": "uuid",
            "function": "create_secret",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION vault.create_secret(new_secret text, new_name text DEFAULT NULL::text, new_description text DEFAULT ''::text, new_key_id uuid DEFAULT NULL::uuid)\n RETURNS uuid\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SECURITY DEFINER\n SET search_path TO ''\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  rec record;\nBEGIN\n  INSERT INTO vault.secrets (secret, name, description)\n  VALUES (\n    new_secret,\n    new_name,\n    new_description\n  )\n  RETURNING * INTO rec;\n  UPDATE vault.secrets s\n  SET secret = encode(vault._crypto_aead_det_encrypt(\n    message := convert_to(rec.secret, 'utf8'),\n    additional := convert_to(s.id::text, 'utf8'),\n    key_id := 0,\n    context := 'pgsodium'::bytea,\n    nonce := rec.nonce\n  ), 'base64')\n  WHERE id = rec.id;\n  RETURN rec.id;\nEND\n$function$\n"
        },
        {
            "args": "secret_id uuid, new_secret text DEFAULT NULL::text, new_name text DEFAULT NULL::text, new_description text DEFAULT NULL::text, new_key_id uuid DEFAULT NULL::uuid",
            "schema": "vault",
            "returns": "void",
            "function": "update_secret",
            "definition": "CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION vault.update_secret(secret_id uuid, new_secret text DEFAULT NULL::text, new_name text DEFAULT NULL::text, new_description text DEFAULT NULL::text, new_key_id uuid DEFAULT NULL::uuid)\n RETURNS void\n LANGUAGE plpgsql\n SECURITY DEFINER\n SET search_path TO ''\nAS $function$\nDECLARE\n  decrypted_secret text := (SELECT decrypted_secret FROM vault.decrypted_secrets WHERE id = secret_id);\nBEGIN\n  UPDATE vault.secrets s\n  SET\n    secret = CASE WHEN new_secret IS NULL THEN s.secret\n                  ELSE encode(vault._crypto_aead_det_encrypt(\n                    message := convert_to(new_secret, 'utf8'),\n                    additional := convert_to(s.id::text, 'utf8'),\n                    key_id := 0,\n                    context := 'pgsodium'::bytea,\n                    nonce := s.nonce\n                  ), 'base64') END,\n    name = coalesce(new_name, s.name),\n    description = coalesce(new_description, s.description),\n    updated_at = now()\n  WHERE s.id = secret_id;\nEND\n$function$\n"
        }
